# Development guidelines

Network Monitor is a single-binary Go app (collector + SQLite + REST/SSE + embedded Svelte SPA). Follow these rules for all code changes.

## Layer boundaries

Data flows in one direction: **collector → store → metrics → api → frontend**.

| Put it here | Not here |
|-------------|----------|
| Ping loop, sample creation (`internal/collector`) | HTTP, UI |
| SQLite I/O, schema (`internal/store`) | Status tiers, HTTP |
| Aggregations, status classification (`internal/metrics`) | SQL, HTTP |
| Routes, handlers, SSE, embed (`internal/api`) | Ping parsing, SQL |
| API client, pure helpers (`web/src/lib`, e.g. `api.ts`, `windows.ts`, `status.ts`, `charts.ts`, `time.ts`, `sse.ts`) | DOM, chart rendering |
| UI components (`web/src/components`) | `fetch`, metric math |

New features land in the correct layer first. If logic is needed in two places, extract to `metrics` or `web/src/lib` — never duplicate across Go and TypeScript.

## API contract sync

- Every JSON shape is defined in Go (with `json` tags) **and** mirrored in `web/src/lib/api.ts`.
- API changes must update **both** in the same change.
- Prefer additive fields over breaking renames.
- SSE events use `{ type, data }` — do not invent a second envelope.
- Update README API table when adding or changing endpoints.

## Test before merge

Run `npm test` from the repo root (Go + Vitest + Playwright) before considering work done.

Add tests for parsing, math, store queries, handlers, and pure TS helpers. Add regression tests when fixing bugs. Do not add tests that only assert mocks or trivial getters.

## Dependencies

Every new dependency needs a one-line justification.

Prefer: Go stdlib, Svelte 5 runes, pure functions, uPlot for charts.
Avoid without strong reason: HTTP frameworks, ORMs, global state libraries, heavy UI/chart libraries.

## Prefer existing patterns

- State in `App.svelte` via runes; components receive props and emit events.
- Window definitions: `DASHBOARD_METRICS` in `web/src/lib/windows.ts`.
- Config in `config.yaml`; secrets via `CONFIG_TOKEN` env only.
- Schema in `internal/store/schema.sql` with forward-only migrations in `store.go`.
- Errors: Go returns up and logs at boundaries; `fetchJson` throws on non-2xx; SSE reconnect stays in `sse.ts`.
- Small focused diffs; one intent per PR; no drive-by formatting.

See [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md) and [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) for full detail.
